202struct API_ElemType {
203
207 API_ElemTypeID typeID;
208
212 API_ElemVariationID variationID;
213
217 API_Guid classID;
218
219 API_ElemType () = default;
220
221 API_ElemType (API_ElemTypeID typeID)
222 : typeID (typeID), variationID (APIVarId_Generic), classID (APINULLGuid)
223 {}
224
225 API_ElemType (API_ElemTypeID typeID, API_ElemVariationID variationID)
226 : typeID (typeID), variationID (variationID), classID (APINULLGuid)
227 {}
228
229 API_ElemType (const API_Guid& classID)
230 : typeID (API_ExternalElemID), variationID (APIVarId_Generic), classID (classID)
231 {}
232
235 API_ElemType &operator= (const API_ElemType &) = default;
236
240 API_ElemType &operator= (API_ElemTypeID newTypeID)
241 {
242 typeID = newTypeID;
243 variationID = APIVarId_Generic;
244 classID = APINULLGuid;
245 return *this;
246 }
247
251 API_ElemType& operator= (const API_Guid& newClassID)
252 {
253 typeID = API_ExternalElemID;
254 variationID = APIVarId_Generic;
255 classID = newClassID;
256 return *this;
257 }
258
262 bool operator== (const API_ElemType& other) const
263 {
264 return typeID == other.typeID && variationID == other.variationID && classID == other.classID;
265 }
266
270 bool operator!= (const API_ElemType& other) const
271 {
272 return !operator== (other);
273 }
274
278 bool operator== (API_ElemTypeID otherTypeID) const
279 {
280 return typeID == otherTypeID;
281 }
282
286 bool operator!= (API_ElemTypeID otherTypeID) const
287 {
288 return !operator== (otherTypeID);
289 }
290
294 bool operator== (const API_Guid &otherClassID) const
295 {
296 return classID == otherClassID;
297 }
298
302 bool operator!= (const API_Guid& otherClassID) const
303 {
304 return !operator== (otherClassID);
305 }
306
310 ULong GenerateHashValue (void) const
311 {
312 return GS::CalculateHashValue (typeID, variationID, classID);
313 }
314
315};
316
321template<>
322struct std::hash<API_ElemType> {
323 std::size_t operator() (const API_ElemType& elemType) const
324 {
325 return elemType.GenerateHashValue ();
326 }
327};
328
330
331inline bool operator== (API_ElemTypeID typeID, const API_ElemType& elemType)
332{
333 return elemType == typeID;
334}
335
336inline bool operator != (API_ElemTypeID typeID, const API_ElemType& elemType)
337{
338 return elemType != typeID;
339}
340
341inline bool operator== (const API_Guid& classID, const API_ElemType& elemType)
342{
343 return elemType == classID;
344}
345
346inline bool operator != (const API_Guid& classID, const API_ElemType& elemType)
347{
348 return elemType != classID;
349}

474class API_ElemPartId {
475public:
476 UInt32 main;
477 UInt32 sub;
478 Int32 floor;
479
480 API_ElemPartId () : main (0), sub (0), floor (0) {}
481
482 bool operator== (const API_ElemPartId& right) const { return (main == right.main && sub == right.sub && floor == right.floor); }
483 bool operator!= (const API_ElemPartId& right) const { return !operator== (right); }
484 ULong GenerateHashValue () const { return (main ^ sub) + floor * 65599; }
485
486};

494typedef enum {
495 API_HatchGlobal = 0,
496 API_HatchRotated = 1,
497 API_HatchDistorted = 2,
498 API_HatchCentered = 3
499} API_HatchOrientationTypeID;
500
501
502#define APIHatchOrinFlag_XAxisGlobal 0x0001 // the fill origin's X coordinate is the global origin's X coordinate
503#define APIHatchOrinFlag_YAxisGlobal 0x0002 // the fill origin's Y coordinate is the global origin's Y coordinate
504#define APIHatchOrinFlag_GlobalOrigo 0x0003
505#define APIHatchOrinFlag_UseInnerRadius 0x0004 // create circular distortion using the innerRadius parameter (API_HatchCentered)
506#define APIHatchOrinFlag_GlobalOrientation 0x0008 // use local orientation, use the distortion matrix, when doesn't set it
507
508#define APIHatchOrinFlag_FitX 0x0010 // (effective for symbol fills only) reset the pattern's X size to the defined X vector's length
509#define APIHatchOrinFlag_FitY 0x0020 // (effective for symbol fills only) reset the pattern's Y size to the defined Y vector's length
510#define APIHatchOrinFlag_KeepProportion 0x0040 // (effective for symbol fills only) keep proportion of symbol fill pattern
511

17870inline void ACAPI_ELEMENT_QUANTITIES_MASK_CLEAR (API_QuantitiesMask &mask)
17871{
17872 memset (&mask, 0, sizeof (mask));
17873}
17878inline void ACAPI_ELEMENT_QUANTITIES_MASK_SETFULL (API_QuantitiesMask &mask)
17879{
17880 memset (&mask, 0xFF, sizeof (mask));
17881}
17882
17887inline void ACAPI_ELEMENT_QUANTITY_MASK_CLEAR (API_QuantitiesMask &mask)
17888{
17889 memset (&mask.elements, 0, sizeof (mask.elements));
17890}
17895inline void ACAPI_ELEMENT_QUANTITY_MASK_SETFULL (API_QuantitiesMask &mask)
17896{
17897 memset (&mask.elements, 0xFF, sizeof (mask.elements));
17898}
17899
17900#define ACAPI_ELEMENT_QUANTITY_MASK_SET(rec,typ,varnam) *((char *) &((rec).elements.typ.varnam)) = -1
17901#define ACAPI_ELEMENT_QUANTITY_MASK_CHECK(rec,typ,varnam) (*((char *) &((rec).elements.typ.varnam)) != 0)
17902
17907inline void ACAPI_ELEMENT_COMPOSITES_QUANTITY_MASK_CLEAR (API_QuantitiesMask &mask)
17908{
17909 memset (&mask.composites, 0, sizeof (mask.composites));
17910}
17911
17916inline void ACAPI_ELEMENT_COMPOSITES_QUANTITY_MASK_SETFULL (API_QuantitiesMask &mask)
17917{
17918 memset (&mask.composites, 0xFF, sizeof (mask.composites));
17919}
17920#define ACAPI_ELEMENT_COMPOSITES_QUANTITY_MASK_SET(rec,varnam) *((char *) &((rec).composites.varnam)) = -1
17921#define ACAPI_ELEMENT_COMPOSITES_QUANTITY_MASK_CHECK(rec,varnam) (*((char *) &((rec).composites.varnam)) != 0)
